description: This fish stew is fragrant with fennel seeds and packed with tender white fish, prawns and baby octopus.
name: Fish, Prawns & Octopus Stew Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 500g white fish fillets, skinless, boneless, chopped into cubes
250g king prawns, peeled and deveined, raw
1 medium onion, peeled and finely sliced

recipeInstructions.text: Heat the oil in a large pan on medium high heat and cook the onions and fennel for 5 minutes, stir in the garlic and fennel seeds and cook for 1 minute.

Pour over the white wine and cook for 1 minute. Tip in the chopped tomatoes, chilli flakes and the white fish and baby octopus. Cook for 4 minutes, add the prawns and cook for 2 minutes or until the seafood is tender and cooked through.
